      "@id": "https://ssbd.riken.jp/repository/ssbd-repos-000405/",
      "@type": "Dataset",
      "identifier": "ssbd-repos-000405",
      "name": "Digital staining of the cell nucleus",
      "description": "The cells were seeded at a concentration of 0.8x10^5 cells/ml in a 35 mm cell culture imaging dish (ibidi, #81156) and incubated in a CO2 incubator for 24 hours. Subsequently, the nuclei were stained with Hoechst 33342 (ThermoFisher, #H3570) according to the manufacturer's protocol. \r\nDataset A consists of differential interference contrast (DIC) images and stained nuclear images of cells used for machine learning. Dataset B includes DIC images and stained nuclear images of cells, along with digitally stained nuclear images.",
